<div id="review_2238402004" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2238402004" />
    <a title="Kaleena" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/75883181-kaleena"><img alt="Kaleena" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1579645979p2/75883181.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2238402004?book_show_action=true">Jan 28, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kaleena" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kaleena" href="/user/show/75883181-kaleena">Kaleena</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/75883181-kaleena?shelf=action-adventure">action-adventure</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/75883181-kaleena?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/75883181-kaleena?shelf=adult-fiction">adult-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/75883181-kaleena?shelf=part-of-a-series">part-of-a-series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/75883181-kaleena?shelf=christian">christian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/75883181-kaleena?shelf=epic">epic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/75883181-kaleena?shelf=political-trouble">political-trouble</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/75883181-kaleena?shelf=map">map</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2238402004" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5038947621131535306">Wow! Epic Christian Fantasy novel that didn&apos;t hold back...yes, please! I actually gave this book 4.5 stars. This world is complex and very well developed. The different people groups, customs and beliefs, histories and cultures are all intricate and fully developed. The plot was action packed and had me guessing more than once. The timing was great and I had know idea we would end up where we did. There were many scenes that I absolutely loved! The beauty of friendship built through trauma was f</span>
  <span id="freeText5038947621131535306" style="display:none">Wow! Epic Christian Fantasy novel that didn't hold back...yes, please! I actually gave this book 4.5 stars. This world is complex and very well developed. The different people groups, customs and beliefs, histories and cultures are all intricate and fully developed. The plot was action packed and had me guessing more than once. The timing was great and I had know idea we would end up where we did. There were many scenes that I absolutely loved! The beauty of friendship built through trauma was fantastic. I enjoyed most all the characters except for Carissa. She drove me insane... Evil was depicted as evil and not glossed over at all. I was surprised by the reality and gruesomeness of evil that this story brought to life. It made this novel feel so real. The characters journey was intense and their transformations were exciting and inspiring to be a part of. From a Christian perspective, the truth of the gospel really shines nicely and I appreciate the enforcement that salvation is never earned, but freely given to all who would receive it. I am very excited to continue forward to the second novel in this series. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5038947621131535306" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


